13. Qc7{ Black protects the bishop and somehow prepares ... c6 - c5 . In general, the right plan. Nevertheless, White should definitely be for choice after normal moves. What Lasker starts to do right now is simply suicidal. }
14. Ne5( 14.O-O { is an easy move. }14...c5!? { is the typical sacrifice - I can only assume that Lasker was nervous about this - but objectively this is good for White. Both, accepting the sacrifice with }15.dxc5 { but also the simple }15.e4 { to stop the capture on  f3  should be enough for a nice edge. } )
14. Nh5{ A very provocate move. But kudos to Schlechter - it worked! }( 14...c5!? { was still possible. } )
15. g4{ A very risky decision to weaken the kingside like that. We will see in the game, that White's king on  e1  will be a problem in the long run. }( 15.f4! { to stabilize the knight is a simple, typical move. Black's last move would have looked quite strange after that. } )
