18. Bc8( 18...c5! { was once again the correct move to activate the bishop. But the position is already so concrete that it would be unfair to the players to criticise their moves on general remarks. } )
19. Rg1( 19.Bxg6?! Be6! { was Black's fantastic idea. White can even win a second pawn with the risky }20.Bxf7+?! Rxf7 21.Qxa6 { but Black will get massive bishops after }21...Bd5! { when  h1  is hanging,  h2  is a problem, and ... e5  to open the second bishop is in the air. } )
