7. Bf5{ This is a very reliable way to develop our pieces. Black will just play ... Ne4 , ... Nd7 , and potentially ... e6  and has no problems. }( 7...e6!? { or }7...b6!? { could lead to pawn structures similar to our  Be2  main lines -  starting here .    }{ The fact that White's knight is not on  c3  but on  d2  and that White has already committed himself to  b3 / Bb2  should make it a decent version for us. } )
8. Be2{ The normal move. White wants to develop and this is the only square available for the bishop. }
