12. Nxb3{ This was played by Nils Grandelius with success.  Taking on  c3  is also not bad. }( 12...Nxc3 13.bxc3 Nxb3 { and here, both...     A)  }14.Qxb3 Qd7! { (If Black exchanges on  b3 , this would give White pawns with very nice central influence), as well as...     B)  }14.axb3 g6 { look okay. } )
13. Qxb3
13. O-O-O{ Slightly risky but very logical. Both  d5  and  b7  are now protected and Black has ideas like ... Qb6  or ... Nc7  to consolidate. White has nothing too threatening and our king might run towards  a8 . }( { Grandelius played }13...Rd8 { and won that game, but after }14.Qxb7 { I found a weird perpetual starting with }14...Nxc3 15.bxc3 Qc4+ 16.Kg1 Qxc3 { and not much to keep the game going. }{     See variation in course  } )
