6. b5{ Once again, it is useful to play this move before White can protect the  d4 -pawn. }
7. Qd3{ Literally forced not to lose the  d4 -pawn. }
7. b4{ This seems to be the strongest move. Black drives away the knight from  c3  and afterwards Black can play a lot of tempi moves like ... Bf5  or ... Ne4 . }( { Another strong move order is the tactical }7...Bf5!? 8.e4 Nxe4! 9.Nxe4 Qd5 { Black will win back the piece and be a pawn up. }10.f3 Bxe4 11.fxe4 Qxg5 { I would take Black any day in this position but the machines insist that White can stay in the game with the stockfishy }12.h4! { . Let me just show how the game might continue here: }12...Qf4! { I think practically the best square. }13.Ne2 Qc7 14.O-O-O!? Bg7 {    }{ I would prefer Black here with moves like ... O-O  and ... c5  coming.     However, I don't want to argue with the machine that claims that the position is equal. } )
8. Na4{ Now, Black’s pieces will all come to life with tempo. }
8. Bf5( 8...Ba6 { is also good. } )
9. Qb3{ Keeping an eye on the knight. }
9. Ne4
10. Nf3( 10.Bf4? Qxd4 { with a mate threat on  f2  is now very annoying. }11.e3?? Qd2# { doesn't help either. } )
10. Qa5( { Threatening   }11...Be6 { . } )
11. Bd2( 11.e3? { runs into }11...Be6! { . } )
11. e5{ A very typical pawn sacrifice. Black's main advantage in this line is their lead in development.     We have to play energetically to use this advantage before White can develop their remaining pieces. }
12. e3( { The most solid response but Black is still much better.     A)  }12.dxe5 Nd7 13.e3 Nxe5-+ { Material is even and Black just has this massive lead in development.     B)    }12.Nxe5 Be6 13.Qd1 Nxd2!-+ { is just horrible for White. White has to recapture with the king and Black will happily hunt this guy down! } )
12. Be6( { An important intermediate move.    The immediate }12...Nxd2 13.Nxd2 exd4 { looks attractive but here White can develop with tempo. }14.Bc4! { and Black is forced in the defensive. } )
13. Qc2
13. Nxd2( { Black could also keep the tension with }13...Bf5 { but }13...Nxd2 { gives us an easy advantage. } )
14. Nxd2
14. exd4
15. exd4( { The most human move is just to recapture but White's problems will not be solved.    The engine just wants to sacrifice the pawn and play }15.Bc4 { to get the pieces out but there is no real discussion that Black is better in the resulting position with the extra pawn after something like }15...dxe3 16.fxe3 Qf5 { .    White has some compensation but not enough. } )
15. Bd5{ This keeps White's pieces boxed in. White has a hard time getting the pieces out. }
