4. g6( {  A)  }5.Nc3 { transposes to the chapter  Royal Adventures .     B)  }5.cxd5 cxd5 6.Nc3 Nc6 { again transposes to the  Schlexchange . } )( {  C)  }5.Bg5 Ne4 { doesn't make a lot of sense here for White. } )
5. e3{ This slow move is also possible with the queen on  b3 . As usual, we follow the rule that we play ... Bg7  and ... O-O  against all kinds of  e2 - e3  setups. }
5. Bg7
6. Nc3{ The most flexible move. }
6. O-O
7. Bd3( { Developing the light-squared bishop allows Black to take on  c4  under decent circumstances. The same reaction can be played against }7.Be2 { .    This is usually the case if White combines these bishop moves with additional tempo-losing moves. }{ If we replace  Qb3  with  h3 , we would play the same way -  see here . With the queen on  b3 , this variation is even better for Black as the queen is nothing but a target. } )
7. dxc4
8. Bxc4
8. b5{ The typical follow-up, gaining space on the queenside. }
9. Bd3{ A slightly more vulnerable square than  e2 , but at least White keeps more control over the central squares. }
9. Nbd7( { A flexible move, preparing  ...c5  as well as  ...e5 . }9...a5 { is possible here as well, but White's queen will have a safe square on  c2  compared to }{ the  line  with   }9.Be2 { . } )
10. O-O
10. a6( { Easy plans for Black. We just try to break with  ...c5 .    }10...Nc5!? { is a funny move that wins the bishop pair but here it costs a pawn. }11.dxc5 Qxd3 12.Ne5 { with a double attack against  d3  and  c6 . Black will have compensation for the pawn but it's just not necessary. } )
11. a4{ A typical response. By attacking  b5 , White makes it harder to push ... c5 . }
11. e5( { So, we just play the other break!    }12.dxe5?! { is not good because of }12...Nc5 { when Black will win the bishop pair without any concessions.    }{ Besides that, Black can either just develop naturally with ... Re8 , ... Qe7 , but we can also just take on  d4  when White either has to live with an IQP on  d4  or they have to give access to the  e5 - and  c5 -square for the  d7 -knight. } )
