9. c5{ A nice immediate counter-strike.     White made some weird moves that don't make a lot of sense in the potentially arising hanging pawn structure if White takes on  c5  and  d5  ( Bd2 ,  Bd3 ,  Qb3 ).     Our next moves are ... Nbd7 , ... Bb7 , ... Qe7 , rooks to  c8  and  d8 . }( { Note that if White goes   }10.dxc5 { , it is a typical idea to go }10...Na6 { , sacrificing a pawn but getting a lot of tempi with ... Nc5  coming. I don't want to analyse this any deeper as }10...bxc5 { is an equally satisfying reply. } )( 9...Nbd7 { is not bad but it allows }10.cxd5 exd5 11.e4 { which isn't really a big deal. But why allow it? } )
