9. Rd1
9. Ne4( { Equality is not Black's biggest problem in this line. Black could also achieve this with moves like }9...Bf5 { or }9...dxc4 { .    Creating as many imbalances as possible was the bigger task for yours truly. However, I am happy with the move }9...Ne4 { . }{ Objectively, this is also equal, but by creating a pawn weakness on  c3 , we'll take a nice first step to give us targets to play against. } )
