12. Nd4{ A good move to block the long diagonal and to not allow ... Bf5  after we have recaptured the pawn with ... Nxc5 . We still have good ways to get access to White's weaknesses. }( { If White plays the greedy }12.c6? { , this is playing with fire. White not only wastes an important tempo, but also opens up more files for Black's pieces. After }12...bxc6 13.dxc6 Bxc3+ 14.Nd2 Nc5 { , Black is only one pawn down and  15...Bf5  is an annoying threat. White should play }15.e4 { to stop this while also overprotecting the  d2 -knight. Still, Black has many good options. }15...e5! { looks like the strongest move to close the  h2 - b8  diagonal and simply plan ... Rb8 - b2 . Objectively, this is already game over. } )( 12.Bc4 { is one of the better moves according to the computer, but looks very innocuous to the human eye as the bishop is just very exposed on  c4 . }12...Qxc5 { looks like the easiest solution as White will lose the  c3 -pawn too very soon. } )
