15. Qxd2+{ I think this is the best way to continue. We have no good way to leave the queens on the board and at least White's king will be slightly awkward dancing in the middle. }
16. Kxd2
16. Rd8+{ I think a good moment to include this check. White is forced to go to  c2  in order not to lose the connection of the rooks where the king is slightly oddly placed. }
17. Kc2
17. Be6{ The position is drawish with the opposite-coloured bishops but there should be some play left. White's extra pawn on  e5  is completely without value and is rather restricting the bishop on  f4 . White has no easy way to get all the rooks off the board.  For our side, it looks reasonable to anchor our light-squared bishop on  b3 . 18... Rd3  would certainly be a good move if it would be our turn but also ... a5 - a4  or ... Rab8  are ideas to prepare this move. }
