9. Be7{ For now, Black just develops normally. }
10. Nge2{ The most flexible move order. The knight always belongs on  e2 . }
10. O-O{ It looks risky to castle into White's pawn storm but there are some points to it.     A very important aspect is the manoeuvre ... Ne8 - d6 . This manoeuvre can be executed in different versions.     If White pushes  h2 - h4 , we can often go ... h5 , threaten to take on  g4 , and if White pushes  g4 - g5 , we can just play ... Ne8  and ... g6  with a pretty safe kingside and we can start our own counterplay on the queenside.     If White postpones  h2 - h4 , ... h5  is not nearly as good. White can keep the tension with  h2 - h3  and the structure stays flexible. }
11. h4{ This is the most popular move. However, Black has a nice strategic concept against it. }
11. Rc8{ Waiting for one more move before going ... h5 . The option does not really run away and ... Rc8  is always a useful move. }( { The immediate }11...h5!? { is very similar. White, however, has more information about Black's kingside setup than in the lines after }11...Rc8 { . } )
12. Kf2{ The main move. White's king has no super safe square on the board in these aggressive lines and  f2  or  g2  are often the destinations White is aiming for. }( 12.h5 { is stopping ... h7 - h5  from Black but White loses control over the  g5 -square. After 12... Ne8  }{ and potentially even ... h6 , it will be tough for White to break Black's dark square blockade. } )( { After other flexible moves such as }12.a3 { , Black can also play }12...h5 { . } )
12. h5{ With the king on  f2 , this move works especially good. White has much less aggressive options.     In the Correspondence game Dessaules - Repp, 2017, White found nothing better than to close the kingside. }
13. g5
13. Ne8{ The knight ideally goes to  d6 . Sometimes it is useful to have the option to put the knight on  g7  to overprotect  h5  against sacrifices. But those are really not a threat here. }
14. Rc1
14. g6{ Black is totally safe on the kingside and can start their counterplay on the queenside. }
