6. Bg4( { I choose the move }6...Bg4 { for different reasons.     1)  It is only the fourth most popular move in this position. That means White players might not be as familiar with this move as with the alternatives }6...Bf5 { , }6...a6 { or }6...e6 { .     2)  If White responds with the most critical move   }7.f3 { , the position will be really imbalanced. Ideal to play for a win!     3)  The move has the best score - pretty much 50%. } )
