11. Nc4{ Anand's move. At some point, White has to choose what to do with the  g1 -knight. }
12. Nf3{ This was played in the game  Aronian - Anand, London 2012 . With the knight on  f3 , Black typically goes ... Bb4 . }( 12.Nge2 { discourages Black to go  ...Bb4 , but Black can usually just start to roll on the queenside after this with }12...b5! { . } )
12. Bb4{ The move we play with White's knight on  f3 . Black gets nice pressure against  c3 . }( {   }13...Nxb2 { is already a threat. } )
13. a3{ White has nothing better. }
13. Bxc3+( { The easiest solution. }13...Qa5 { is certainly also worth a look. } )
14. bxc3
14. Bb5{ Occupying the  f1 - a6  diagonal before White can stop this with  a3 - a4 .     Black will just continue development with ... O-O  but in the long run, we will be happy if we can exchange the light-squared bishops and we will try to put pressure along the c-file. }
