14. Qe2{ This is not really threatening to take on  c4 . With the weak pawn on  c3 , this is often not more than an exchange where White loses the bishop pair. }( 14.Qf3 { The most forcing move. By pinning the  d5 -pawn, White is threatening }-- 15.Bxc4 { and also stops  14...Bb7  because of this.   }14...Ba6! { however, unpins the d5-pawn and threatens some discoveries such as }-- 15...Nd2 { to win the bishop pair.    Arguably   }15.Qe2 { is now the best move when Black can even just transpose to our trainable with }15...Bb7!? { . } )
