11. Na4{ With the idea to invade via  b6 . This makes our ... Re8 /... Bf8  plan less attractive as the queen has more escape squares.     But by moving away the knight from the center, there is less pressure and we can develop in an even simpler way. }
11. Bf5{ By developing the bishop, Black makes the invasion on  b6  very innocuous. Next, we can play ... Rc8  or ... b5 . }( 11...Re8? 12.Qb6! { +- should be avoided. }-- 13.Bc7 { is a threat but also }13.Qxd8 Rxd8 { , followed by }14.Bc7 { or }14.Nb6 Ra7 15.Bb8 { . Let's use the rest of the trainable to show why White shouldn't occupy the  b6 -square. } )
