15. Nf3( { The best square for the knight.     A)  }15.Nd7!? { is a funny-looking move but not really doing anything.     A1)  Even if we play the simple }15...Qxd7 16.Qxa5 { and now either }16...e5 { , }16...Rc2 { or the crazy engine suggestion }16...g5!? 17.hxg5 fxg5 18.Bxg5 Qf5! { followed by }-- ...Rc2 { . we are always fine.     A2)  The move }15...Nc4 { might be an even smarter move to trade the knights. After }16.Bxc4 Qxd7 17.Be2 a6 { , Black is just completely fine. } )( {  B)  }15.Ng4 { is just a weird square with no real purpose. }15...Rc2⇆ { gives us active counterplay. } )
