11. O-O( { The most normal move. }11.Rc1 { leads to a variation from the  7.Rc1 move order . } )
11. g5{ Now, Black is ready to go after the bishop! }
12. Bxc6{ If White wants to go for the  Ne5  idea, they have to take on  c6  first. }
12. bxc6
13. Ne5{ The logical follow-up. }
13. Bxe5{ Forced as White was attacking  h5  and  c6  both. White can now take both on  e5  or on  h5 . }
14. dxe5
14. Ng7( { There is no need to ruin our pawn structure with }14...gxh4 { . }{ Our knight will come to  f5  and we just have very nice control in the center. } )
15. Bg3
15. Be6( { This is slightly more flexible than the immediate }15...Nf5 { as Black also prepares ideas with ... c5 . } )
16. Na4{ The only move if White wants to fix the weak pawn on  c6  and the weak square on  c5 . }( 16.Rc1 c5 { is too slow for White. } )
16. d4{ A nice pawn sacrifice. Black opens up the  Be6 , gets a nice square on  d5  and ... dxe3  is an idea to spoil White's structure. }( { The idea is that }17.exd4 Nf5! { will just win back the pawn. } )
