10. Nd2{ This is a solid move. White tries to avoid the chaos combined with ... g5  by keeping an eye on the  h5 -knight. }
10. O-O{ The most flexible move. }
11. f4{ This move secures the  e5 -outpost for White. Black should create rather concrete counterplay before White gets a long-term grip in the position. }
