13. Nb5{ There is not really anything better. }
13. Qxd3
14. Rxb4
14. Qxd1
15. Rxd1{ White still has compensation but Black is solid with their extra pawn. A good way to get the pieces into the game seems to be by winning some space with the a-pawn. }
15. a5
16. Rb2
16. a4{ Black has ideas like ... Ra5 , ... Ne4 , ... Bd7  and should never be in any danger here. }
