10. Ne4{ We have to disturb White's piece coordination before White can just consolidate. Black is just threatening to remove the defender of the  b5 -bishop by playing ... Ne4xc3 .     White should now protect the bishop on  b5  and has different ways to do so. }( { Playing }11.Bxc6 bxc6 { is not very principled as White just gives away the bishop pair,  b2  is still hanging and Black has even ideas to keep the white king in the center with ... Ba6 . } )
11. Qb3{ This move does not only protect  b5  but is also attacking the  d5 -pawn. However, as we will see, Black doesn't have to worry too much about this attack. }
11. Nxc3( { We should take now as   }12.Nxd5 { was a threat. } )
12. bxc3{ Taking with the pawn is possible but gives Black the typical counterplay along the c-file and the weak  c4 -square. }
12. Na5{ Coming with tempo and useful as we are controlling  c4 . }
13. Qb4{ doesn't have the disadvantage of allowing ...  b7 - b5  with tempo but Black still has good ways to make use of the  c4 -square. }
13. Be6{ Often a good square for the bishop in this structure. Black has the easy plan of putting a rook on the c-file and jumping with the knight to  c4  at some point. }
14. Ng5{ This, followed by the next move is the only way to somehow disturb Black's plan. }( { After a normal move like }14.O-O { Black can already get a slightly more comfortable position with }14...a6 15.Be2 Qxb4 16.cxb4 Nc4! { and this knight is very annoying on  c4 . White cannot easily get rid of it, especially because }17.Ng5 Bd7! { makes it still impossible to take twice on  c4  because of ... Bb5 -ideas. } )
14. Bf5{ Black should be happy with the inclusion of the last two moves from a positional point of view. The knight doesn't belong to  g5  but White can follow up with a concrete idea. }
15. g4
15. Bc8{ White tries to push Black's pieces back to bad squares. But this comes with a high price:  The kingside is much weaker now and especially ...  f7 - f5  is a very attractive hook for Black. }( { For example }16.O-O f5!? { already looks somewhat risky for White. } )
