11. Bg7{ A solid continuation. White can win back their pawn on  c4  and is slightly more active.  However, we have the better pawn structure. }( 11...e5 { invites some crazy variations that are rather unnecessary. Let me just show you the main line. }12.Nf3 Bf5! 13.e4!? { Not objectively dangerous but this spices things up. }13...Bxe4 14.Qxe4 Qxc3+ 15.Ke2 Qxa1 16.Bxe5 { White is threatening both queen and rook. }16...Qa2+ 17.Nd2 { For some reason the only move. }17...Nc6 18.Bxh8+ Be7 { Even though White is a piece up, there is nothing better than the following sequence. If the middlegame continues, White's king on  e2  is in trouble. }19.Qxc4 Qxc4+ 20.Nxc4 f6! { Black will win back the bishop with }-- ...Kf7 { and reach an equal endgame. } )
