6. Be6{ Black should definitely defend the  c4 -pawn - otherwise 5... dxc4  wouldn't have made a lot of sense - and this is the most stubborn way to do so. }( 6...b5?! { After this, White can win back the pawn and has chances for an advantage with their better central control: }7.a4 b4 8.Nb1 Ba6 9.Qc2⩲ { with a slight advantage. } )
