15. Bc4{ The safest square. }( 15.Be6?! Nxd4 16.Bxd4 Qxd4 { is a problem for White. }17.Rd1 ( { ( }17.O-O Qe5 { is creating threats against  h2 . }18.Rfe1?! Be3!-+ { is a funny motif to open up the rook.) } )17...Qe5+ { This check forces White's king to  f1  when White has no harmony between their pieces. }18.Kf1 g3!∓ { A nice move to open even more files on the kingside. White is in quite some trouble. } )
15. g3{ Even better than taking on  d4 . We undermine the protection of the  e3 -bishop and put pressure on White's pawns. }( 15...Nxd4 16.Bxd4 Qxd4 17.Rd1 Qe5+⩱ { is still better for Black but at least White can play }18.Be2 { . } )
16. h3{ A bad move but others simply allow Black to win the pawn on  h2  with simple means. }( {  A)  }16.Bxh6+ { is the best option. It makes sense to slightly misplace Black's rook. }16...Rxh6 17.O-O-O Qc7!⩱ { Activating the queen with tempo as }-- ...Na5 { is a threat.    Next, we will simply take on }h2 { with a slightly better position. White has nothing better.     B)  For example, }16.O-O-O { is also losing the  h2 -pawn but Black can play many tempi moves first. }16...Bxe3+ 17.fxe3 Na5! { Getting the bishop. }18.Qa4 Nxc4 19.Qxc4 gxh2-+ { Material is even but the pawn on  h2  is very annoying for White - many endgames will simply be losing - and when it comes to attacking in the middlegame. Our queenside play with ... Rc8  and pushing the pawns also comes pretty fast. } )
16. Ng4( { A beautiful shot to disturb White's setup. White loses all stability.    For example,     A)  }17.hxg4?! Bxe3 { makes matters worse. }18.Rxh8 Bxf2+ 19.Kf1 Qxh8-+ { with a winning attack.     B)    }17.Bxh6+ Rxh6 { The threat against  f2  is huge. }18.fxg3 Nxd4-+ { , followed by }-- ...Ne3 { is also just horrible. White's king won't survive.     C)    }17.Nd1 { is a very passive move to stabilise  e3  and  f2 . Black can still break through. }17...gxf2+ 18.Bxf2 Nxf2 19.Nxf2 Nxd4-+ { White is only one move away from castling but they still won't make it. ... Rc8  and ... Qa5 + are coming. }20.Qc3 Rc8 { would threaten  ...b5  and even after }21.a4 e5 { , White couldn't castle because of }22.O-O Ne2+ { . } )
