12. f6{ Black has to go for this move to drive away the knight. }( { A move like }12...cxd5?! { looks very natural to create counterplay in the center. Unfortunately, the engine proves that White has convincing ways to punish Black's lack of development. A sample line could be }13.exd5 Bb7 14.axb5 Qxd5 15.Qxd5! { White can even trade queens. }15...Bxd5 16.Be3+- { when the  a7 -pawn will fall and White's passer should be decisive. } )
