11. Bd2{ There are not that many independent tries in this  10.Qc4  setup. This is White's best attempt as it provokes ... a5  after which White can go for the  g3 -setups without worries about ... Qa5  motifs - like in the last variation. }( {  A)  }11.Qxb4 { transposes to the lines  starting here . } )( {  B)  }11.e3 { should also transpose if White takes on  b4  on the next move. However, with the dark-squared bishop locked in, it is also usually okay for Black to play  ...a5  quickly and keep the material balanced with an overall okay position. For example }11...O-O 12.Be2 a5 { is okay for Black. } )
