12. Nbd7{ Black just develops naturally. Soon, ... e5  or ... c5  will be playable. }
13. Nc3( { As we will see in the next lines, Black will get active counterplay after }13.Be2 Nd5 { . }{ So it looks logical to anticipate the knight move. However, this move is too slow and Black has several ways to get very nice compensation. } )
13. c5{ A principled reaction. White just gave up the control over  c5  and we immediately take advantage of that. }( {  A)  }13...e5 14.dxe5 Ng4 { also seems to promise Black enough piece activity for the pawn. Even the move that White anticipated with their last move, is fully reasonable. } )( {  B)  }13...Nd5!? 14.Nxd5 cxd5 { is also possible. Black is ready to open the center with }-- ...e5 { .    So overall, we are really spoilt for choice. } )
14. Qa3{ This is White's best move according to the engines. }( 14.dxc5 { is also playable but Black can win the pawn back under very decent circumstances. }14...Qc7 { One of different solid moves to win back the c-pawn. }15.Be2 Nxc5 16.O-O Rfc8 { Black has a lot of pressure for the pawn as White has problems untangling their queenside. ... Rab8 , ... Nfe4 , maybe even ... Bd3  to install an octopus on  d3  might be ideas to improve our position. } )
14. cxd4{ Forcing White to decide on how to recapture. }
15. exd4{ After this move, Black has a very aggressive series of moves to open many files. }
15. e5{ Nice attacking chess. We are happy about every open file and this is not even an additional sacrifice. }
16. dxe5( 16.Be2 e4 { can quickly become dangerous for White. It is also not so easy to keep the extra pawn for example: }17.Nd2 Nb6 { with the threat of }-- ...Qxd4 { . Or }17.Ne5 Nxe5 18.dxe5 Nd5 { when  e5  is weak. } )
16. Nxe5{ Black will win back the piece. }
17. Nxe5
17. Re8
18. Be2{ White shouldn't try to keep the piece but instead should go for quick castling. }( 18.f4 Ng4-+ { is just the start of a massive attack for Black.  ...f6  is a threat but we might also just take on  e5  with a piece and go for mate! } )( 18.Bf4 Nd5-+ { is not even keeping the piece. } )
18. Rxe5
19. O-O{ White's king is in safety but we'll still have a lot of compensation with our active pieces. }
19. Nd5{ Trying to get to the second rank. }
20. Nxd5
20. Rxe2{ Black's bishop pair and active pieces give us easily enough compensation. }
