14. Rb8{ Black had some pressure in  Salvador - Hübner, Italy 2010 .     Black's pieces are more active and White's d and c-pawn are currently the weakest pawns on the board. Black might just continue with ... Qa5 , ... Rfd8 , regrouping the  f6 -knight so that the butcher becomes happier - ... Ne8 - d6  or ... Nd7 - b6  look logical. }
