10. c5{ This was once played in  Sachdev-Krush . White seems to be more or less lost after this move as their center cannot sustain its own weight. }
10. Bg4( { Black is simply threatening   }11...Ne4 { with the double threat of winning the  d4 -pawn but also playing }-- ...Nxc5 { . } )
11. Nbd2{ The most stubborn defence. White takes control of  e4  and supports the knight on  e4 . }
11. Nh5{ A typical move in this pawn structure. The knight is heading towards  f4  and the butcher gets opened up. }
12. h3{ Trying to get rid of the annoying bishop on  g4 . }
12. Nf4{ A nice intermediate move. }
13. Bc2( 13.Bb5 Bxd4! { is already winning a pawn for Black. For example: }14.Bxd4 Nxd4 15.hxg4 Nxb5 { . } )
