13. Bxd7( 13.Rc5? { just doesn't work here for White. }13...Na6! { attacks the rook and White has no good square. The rook will always be in an awkward spot. }14.Nc4 { Comes with tempo but cuts the escape route for the rook. }( { ( }14.Re5 { Squares on the fifth rank are just weird. For example here, Black has }14...Be6 { with  ...Nd5  ideas.) } )14...Qd8 { We can just go back. The unfortunate placement of the rook on  c5  forced White to at least give up the bishop pair with }15.Bxa6 Rxa6∓ { Bishop pair plus pawn majority should give Black a close to winning position. } )
