12. Ne4{ A beautiful exchange sacrifice but not even the only move. To be honest, there is not much risk involved as Black will win the exchange back very soon. }( 12...Re8 { leads to similar positions. White can win a pawn temporarily but Black will just take over the c-file soon and invade White's camp. }13.Bxf6 ( { ( }13.Ba3 Ne4-+ { cannot be allowed.) } )13...Bxf6 { White is a pawn up but how does White get their pieces out? Especially the knight on  d2  looks dumb. Black can just regroup the dark-squared bishop to the queenside and force White to give up some squares to invade.    For example: }14.Be2 Nd7 15.O-O Be7! { A nice manoeuvre. }16.Nb1 { Yeah, this looks dumb but do you have a better move? }16...Rec8 17.Qd2 { Even the queen trade doesn't help White. }17...Qxd2 18.Nbxd2 Ba3! 19.Rxc8+ Rxc8∓ { White is still tied down and Black's rook is about to land on  c2 . } )
