9. a3{ The most popular move on amateur level. }
9. Ne4( { Not the only move but as in other variations as well, I like this move to create imbalances.    Either we take on  c3  to imbalance the pawn structure, }10.Bd2 Nxd2 { grabs the bishop pair and   }10.Nxe4 dxe4 11.Nd2 e5! { is also a good start to get active counterplay. An instructive continuation is }12.dxe5 Bf5 { We protect  e4  before recapturing the e5-pawn. }13.e6!? { A tricky response that wins a pawn but Black gets massive compensation. }13...Bxe6! { A strong move. }( { ( }13...fxe6? 14.g4+- { wins a piece.) } )14.Nxe4 Qb6=∞ { White is a pawn up but with the pressure against  b2 , and the open c- and d-file, Black has wonderful compensation. White has a hard time developing. } )
