16. Nxd5{ This is White's best move but Black will win back the pawn on  d4  back. }
16. Nxd5( { Black has to exchange the knights first.    }16...cxd4? 17.Be7!± { is a cute tactic that Black should not allow. Black cannot take twice on  e7  as  a8  is hanging in the end. } )
17. Qxd5
17. cxd4{ Creating a weakness on  d4 . }
18. exd4
18. Nb6( { White loses the  d4 -pawn and }19.Qxb7 Qxd4 { is also not ideal for White as  a3 ,  d3  and  a1  are all under pressure. } )
