13. Qa5{ This seems to be a good move concretely. The queen leaves the d-file, so it is easier to execute the ... c5  or ... e5  break.  a2  might also be a problem with no rook left on  a1 . }( 13...b5 { is also possible but I am not sure if I am happy with Black's position if White just takes on  d5 . }14.cxd5 { If we play }14...cxd5 { , we have a playable but slightly boring exchange where both sides have their pieces on bad squares. After }14...exd5 { , we have a typical Carlsbad structure but the  ...b5  move looks slightly unprovoked and White might have some pressure by putting the rooks on the c-file. } )
