12. Nbd7( { Black is ready to play   }13...e5 { . } )
13. e4{ The only move directed against our easy plan. }( { After something like }13.b5 { , }13...e5! { is creating great counterplay. The immediate threat is }-- { ... }e4 { but if White anticipates this, we can also just go }14...Re8 { , }-- 15...exd4 { , ... Nd7 - f8 - e6  with counterplay against  d4 . } )
13. dxe4
14. Bxe4{ Maybe not the intuitive way to recapture but Black should not take the bishop as White's knight comes quickly to  d6 . }
14. Nd5{ A good positional move. We are attacking the  b4 -pawn but we are also fine to play ... Nxc3  and ... Nd7 - f6 - d5  with a massive outpost. }( { Don't go }14...Nxe4? 15.Nxe4!± { when White has ideas like }-- 16.Bg5 { or }16.Nd6 { . } )
