12. Rac1( { This leads to very similar positions as }12.Be1 { . Black can play the same setup and White usually plays the bishop move later anyways to anticipate Black's breaks. } )
12. Qe7{ Black is once again getting ready for ... e5 . }
13. Qe2( { White's main move.     A)  }13.Be1 e5 { is Black's idea. If White takes on  d4 , we go  ...e4 . } )( {  B)  Against }13.Bf1 { , I would again recommend }13...dxc4 14.Bxc4 e5 { with active counterplay. } )
13. a6{ With the same counterplan ideas as in the last trainable: ... b5 , ... dxc4  and then ... b5 , ... c5  or ... e5 . }( { Actually, }14.Be1 { - which is the main move - would transpose to one sample variation from the  last trainable . } )
