10. Nbd7{ Typical: Black wants to play ... e6 - e5 . In the best case without allowing  c4xd5 . }
11. b3{ Typically, White wants to develop their bishop to  b2  with this move but it also allows to recapture on  c4  with the pawn if Black ever takes. }
11. Re8{ A good square for the rook. If White goes  cxd5 , our rook will be on the open file immediately and also ... e6 - e5  is supported. }
12. Bb2{ This is the most logical follow-up of White's last move. }
