13. a6{ Black's general idea is simple: The knight on  e5  cannot be allowed there forever and because ... f6  is too weakening here and Black has no good follow-up, we have to take on  e5  at some point.  After that, we have to play ... f6  to bring our bishop on  g7  to life. However, it is important to control the  b5 -square before doing so, because  Nc3 - b5  can be an annoying move in a lot of positions.     This whole line with  8.cxd5  and  9.Ne5  is considered one of White's best ways to play against  7...b6 , so let's let's see how Black can procceed. }( 13...Nxe5 14.dxe5 f6?! { would be typical but White has the annoying }15.Nb5 { This threatens  16.Nc7  }{ with the double threat  Nxa8  and  Ne6 . }15...Rc8 { is a nice try because White cannot win the  a7 -pawn without losing  e5  but White just plays }16.Nd4 { with a dominant knight while the threat }-- 17.Ne6 { is still annoying. } )
