16. Qd4
16. Bc8{ Once again, a solid move. We take care of the threat against  b6  and play ... f6  at the next best opportunity. For example: }
17. b4
17. f6{ Finally, we are able to play this break and activate the butcher. Black gets nice counterplay. }
