9. Ne5{ This is the main move. White establishes a strong knight on  e5  and is often ready to support it with  f2 - f4 . }
9. Ne4( { Black can also start with }9...Bb7 { in this position, but ... Ne4  is a key idea against White's setup with the knight on  e5 . We don't really care about White's option to take on  e4  and this move has a lot of advantages:     - It opens up the butcher     - it prepares .... f6      - whenever we take on  e5  with the  b8 -knight (after ... Nbd7  or ... Nc6 ), the recapture is not with tempo - we have the idea to take on  c3  and create an imbalanced pawn structure. } )
