14. Ba3
14. Rc8
15. Rc1
15. Qd7{ Connecting the rooks. }
16. Qd2( 16.Ne5 Qe6 { doesn't give White anything. } )
16. Rfd8
17. Rc2
17. Nd5
18. Rfc1
18. Qf5{ Bringing the queen to the kingside. Slowly but surely, Black can try to poke White with ... h5 - h4 - h3  ideas.  Potentially even the g-pawn might join the fray. ... e7 - e5  might not be easy to play as long as White's knight is on  c4  but it is certainly also a decent idea.  Overall, Black's position is just very harmonious. }
