11. h4{ A principled idea. If White reacts to the pressure against  c4 , Black gets the structures that they is aiming for. With this move, White just ignores the pawn and tries to soften Black's kingside with  h4 - h5  and then most likely  hxg6 . }
11. Qc7{ White's h-pawn advance is not really the start of a massive kingside attack, so we should just develop our pieces. This move is necessary in order to do so.  Black has to stabilize their queenside pawns. }( {  A)  }11...Bxc4?! 12.Bxc4 dxc4 13.axb6± { leaves Black with a horrible structure. } )( {  B)  The immediate }11...Nd7?! { allows the strong exchange sacrifice }12.axb6 axb6 13.Rxa6 Rxa6 14.cxd5 { followed by  dxc6 . } )
12. cxd5{ This might be one of the better versions for White to go  cxd5  because the knight on  a6  can not easily be regrouped via  c7  and so White does at least win some time. }
12. cxd5
13. Bxa6
13. Nxa6
14. Qd3{ White brings their pieces with tempo to good squares but Black's structure is just extremely solid. Even with this head start, it is not easy for White to prove anything before Black coordinates. }
14. Qb7{ Protects  a6  and gives the  c7 -square for the knight. }
15. Ba3{ I think the most logical move. White fights against ... Nc7  and forces Black to lose even more time to get their desired setup. }
15. Rfe8{ Another move that is not part of our plan because the rook is not doing too much on  e8  but it illustrates the solidness of Black's structure. White really won a lot of tempi compared to similar variations but Black just continues to claim that their position will be extremely solid if they only get in moves like ... Nc7 , ... Qc6  and potentially ... b5 . }
16. h5( { White certainly has other moves as well like }16.Rab1 { or }16.Rfb1 { but Black's setup is always similar and this move seems to be the most logical to me. } )
16. Nc7{ It took us some time but now the knight is finally away from the silly  a6 -square. Our next move will ideally be something like ... Qc6  and potentially ... b5  to stabilize the queenside.  If White takes on  b6 , Black will fight for the a-file. }
