12. Ne2{ This does look like a pretty random square but it might actually be the most challenging move. There is no big point behind it, it's just that the alternatives had small problems: }( 12.Ne4 { mainly led to an exchange of knights that opened up the  g7 -bishop while }12.Na4 { couldn't create a real blockade on  c5  anyway and was only leading to some tempo moves for Black. } )
