14. Bc4{ The best move. White takes the chance to keep the bishop on the board. }( 14.e4 { is a logical move, since }b7 { plays a role for Black in many variations, but now }14...Nxd5 { is simply a good move. }15.exd5 ( { ( }15.Qxd5?! Qxd5 { is simply good for Black. Since otherwise the  e4  pawn would hang, White has to play }16.exd5 { , but after }16...f5 { and }-- ...e4 { the white strategy has failed to restrict the butcher.) } )15...Rc8 { looks like a good move to stabilize the knight on  c5  before playing  ...e4 . }16.Be3 e4! { Again, this is the typical move that breathes life into our pieces.    On the next move we can cover the pawn with  ...Re8  or even  ...f5 . }17.Bxc5 Rxc5 { leads to nothing, since White loses the d-pawn when he takes out on  e4 . } )
14. e4{  Aronian - Yu, Grand Prix Riga 2019 . This is the move in principle. Black gains space and opens the long diagonal. In the next moves, we play  ...Qe7  and put our rooks on the c and d files. }
