13. Re8{ Again, Black gets ready to kick the bishop away from  f3  with ... e5 - e4 . }
14. Re1{ This move has been played in practice in most games and reliably stops ... e5 - e4  for the moment. }
14. Bf8{ Another position where the butcher can be regrouped. We keep the  d6 -square in Black, so White has to think twice about playing  d5 - d6 .  Apart from that, we are looking for active play with ... a6 , ... b5 ,  ...Rc8  and possibly sometimes  ...Bc5 .  ...e4  remains an important resource in the black game, but at least none of our pieces are dependent on the move being played anymore. }( 14...Nc5 { is a possibility and prepares  ...e4 . But at least the knight can't hop from  d7  to  e5  in the resulting structure.    }14...Rc8 { is a flexible move that doesn't commit to anything and also fits in any situation. } )
