14. Nb6{ The d-file looks a bit dangerous at first glance, but White doesn't have a particularly great discovery. }
15. Nc3{ This is still the best move, relatively speaking. }( {  A)  }15.Nxf6+ Qxf6 { causes no problems. White can't really win the  e4 -pawn. }16.Qxe4 { plays with fire. }( { ( }16.Bb3 { is safer, but }16...Qxf4 17.exf4 Rfd8 { doesn't give any advantage either.) } )16...Rfe8 17.Qg4 h5 18.Qe2 Nxc4 19.Qxc4 Rad8 { and Black has a wonderful version of typical compensation as we will see later in the chapter. White has given away many moves with the queen }{ . }( {  B)  }15.Nxb6?? Qxd1+-+ { as a small reminder that the  d1 -rook is not protected:) } ) )
