20. Rac8( { It threatens   }21...Rxc1+ { . } )
21. Qb4{ White should cover the  d2  rook to take this tactic out of the position. }( {  A)  }21.Kh2 { prevents capturing  c1  with check, but it is a less active way to defend against the threat. }21...a5!? { Black can simply spread out on both wings, for example. }21...h5!? { is also possible }{ . }( {  B)  }21.Rxd8+ Rxd8 22.Qf3 Rd3 { leads to the comment on the last move. } ) )
21. Qe5{ Black improves the queen so that both  ...a5  is an idea and the development of the  c1 -bishop is further complicated because the pressure on  b2  increases. Black has full compensation. }
