14. Rd8{ Creating some ideas along the d-file. With queen and rook on the same file, we have ideas with ... c5 , ... e5  or even .... f5  first, followed by ... e5 . }
15. Qd2{ Connecting the rooks and stopping ... e5  for now. }
15. Ndc7{ A typical move. Black is renewing the idea to go ... e5  - maybe after ... f5  first to not let the knight to  d6 . Besides that, we can bring our knight to  e6  to attack  d4  and free the  c7 -square for the other knight.  Black has a nice position. }
