11. bxc6{ Going for the imbalanced structure. Black's pressure against the b-file is a compensating factor and Black will usually easily achieve ... e7 - e5  to strike back in the center. }
12. Na4{ By far the best move. The knight protects  b2 , attacks the queen and takes control over the  c5 -square which is usually a good thing to make sure that the  c6 -pawn remains a weakness. }
12. Qa6{ An interesting square. It might look weird at first glance to allow  Na4 - c5  with tempo but it is not clear if the knight is really better on  c5  and than on  a4 .      a4  is a pretty good square as it also protects  b2  and on  c5 , the knight would be undermined after a potential ... e5 .     Besides this, the queen does a nice job to keep an eye on  e2 . Especially in combination with ... Rfe8  and ... e5 , White might have to deal with the  e2 -pawn at some point. }
13. Re1{ Let's use this as a sample line to illustrate Black's plan as this was played in the most recent and highest-rated correspondence game that I could find with this position. It is just useful to overprotect  e2  for the future. }( 13.Nc5 Qb5 { doesn't change much about Black's plan to go ... Rfe8  and ... e5 . } )
