11. Bf5{ Developing the bishop and attacking the knight. We will play 12... Nbd7  on the next move and all our pieces are on good squares while White struggles with a very passive queenside coordination. Note that the bishop will now be pretty safe on  f5  because there is no knight on  e5  that could potentially support  g3 - g4 . }
