12. cxd5
12. Nxd5{ There was nothing wrong with ... cxd5 , but Black can already rely on their active piece play in this Grünfeld structure. White's  e3 - e4  is possible, but doesn't win material because of the in-between moves ... Nc3  and ... Nb5 . }
13. Nh4{ This move has been played in the majority of cases but also not too successful. }
13. Be6{ Black usually proceeds with ... Nc7  which is a nice move to increase the pressure on  b3  and to prepare ... Nb5  .... Nc3  would also be a strong move if White does nothing against it. Black simply has active piece play and things can easily go wrong for White.  I recommend checking out the Model game Pilgram - Almeraya -  see here . }
