13. Bf2{ This is the engine's top choice so let's use this as mainline. White protects the  e3 -pawn with the bishop. Black will play similar for similar compensation as after  12...a5  but we will have two unopposed bishops and we can take away the  e5 -square for White's knight with ... f6 . }( 13.Qe2?! { protects  e3  but is just running into one of Black's main resources. }13...a5! { ∓, followed by }-- ...Ba6 { . } )
