14. b3{ White has to deal with the attack against the b-pawn. }( 14.b3 { seems to me like the most precise move because Black might provoke this move later anyways.    For example }14.Qc2 Qb6 { would force White to waste another tempo with the b-pawn. } )
14. a5{ Black prepares ... Ba6  to fight for the long diagonal. }
15. O-O{ The most natural move. Finally, White has one tempo to castle. }( 15.h3 { leads to a similar position. Black will take the bishop on  f2  and occupy the  f1 - a6  diagonal. }15...Nxf2 16.Kxf2 Ba6=∞ { Black's pieces are very active. White cannot really do something constructive in this position because every pawn move would rather be suicidal than anything else.  Black's bishops are only waiting for a moment to become even more active! So Black has a lot of potential to just shuffle around with their pieces. If you prefer a concrete plan, building up the rooks on the c-file and eventually opening up the position with ... cxd4  is certainly one straightforward idea. Either, we will create a weakness on  c3  or - if White plays  cxd4  - we invade via the c-file and the weak dark squares (... Bb4  or ... Ba3 ) } )
15. Ba6{ Occupying the nice long diagonal. }
16. Re1{ A logical move, not making any concessions with the pawn structure. }( { Technically, White can play }16.c4 { but this is also risky. If the center explodes, this should be advantageous for the side with the two bishops. Certainly, a decent idea is just to anticipate this and put the rooks on  c8  and  d8 . }16...Rfd8 17.h3 Nxf2 18.Rxf2 Rbc8⩱ { Something like this looks like a logical setup. Eventually, we will take on  c4  and/or  d4 . } )
16. Nxf2{ White had the  e3 -pawn protected and was ready to move the  f2 -bishop next. This is not our intention! We want to play with two bishops versus two knights. }
17. Kxf2
17. Rfc8{ Black has a lot of pressure on the queenside. White cannot really do something active and can merely wait.  Black can just slowly improve the position, ... Bd6 , ... Rc7 , ... Qb6  look like typical shuffle moves.     Eventually, we can take on  d4  and try to invade on the queenside. }
