11. e4{ The most logical reply. White stops the threat and goes for the exchange of one of Black's central pawns. }
11. Bg4{ The type of the position is similar to the last trainable. The additional central influence - even after an exchange on  d5 , do just give us the slightly easier play.  White also some concrete things to worry about. ... Rad8  and ... d4  can be really annoying because of the pin of the  f3 -knight and the stacked minor pieces on the d-file.  If White moves their queen out of the pin, ... Bxf3  becomes an option. If White recaptures with the knight, we can take on  e4 , following it up with ... f5  and ... e4  and a nice kingside initiative. }
