8. f4{ This so-called Stonewall setup secures nice control over one colour-complex - here the dark squares - but creates some weaknesses on the light squares. Black can immediately try to exploit those. }
8. cxd4{ A nice capture. Often, White wants to recapture on  d4  with the e-pawn in these structures to make use of the open e-file but this is not possible here as the  f4 -pawn would be hanging.  In the resulting position, Black can immediately try to invade on the queenside. }
9. cxd4( 9.exd4? Qxf4∓  )
