10. Ngf3{ This does allow Black's idea. }
10. Nb4{ This was Black's idea. }( 10...Ng4!? { is a move to implement the  ...Nb4  idea with slightly different piece placement. After }11.Qe2 Nb4! 12.Bb1 { , Black can try to play }...Rc8 { to invade via  c1  or  c2  and Black can play }...Qa6 { to exchange one of White's defenders of the light squares. Also a decent line for Black! } )
11. Bb1{ Staying on the  f1 - a6  diagonal is not possible. }( 11.Be2? Ng4 { or }11...Rc8 { win. } )
11. Bb5{ With a very annoying bishop for White to deal with. It will not be so easy for White to castle while Black can just play easily with ... O-O  and ... Rac8 . }( { If White plays a move like }12.a3 { , we can either invade with }12...Nd3+ { but it is also completely okay to just drop back with }12...Nc6 { and enjoy White's struggle on the light squares. } )
