8. cxd4{ A nice capture. Often, White wants to recapture on  d4  with the e-pawn in these structures to make use of the open e-file but this is not possible here as the  f4 -pawn would be hanging.  In the resulting position, Black can immediately try to invade on the queenside. }
9. cxd4( 9.exd4? Qxf4∓  )
9. Bd7{ Black is getting ready for ... Nb4  and ... Bb5 . }
10. a3{ The usual reply. White spends a tempo to prevent ... Nb4 . }
10. Ne7{ The start of a very nice manoeuvre. The knight on  c6  wasn't doing too much anymore and blocking the c-file. Now, we are heading to  f5 .     It is important to note that White does never want to exchange their bishop on  f5  in these Stonewall structures as the light -squares would become even more vulnerable and the open e-file after ... exf5  can be used to target  e3 . White cannot even block that pressure with  Nf3 - e5  because the knight can be potentially kicked away with ... f6 .     On  f5 , the knight attacks  e3  but it is also an important idea to land on  d6  eventually where it controls all the light squares and helps prepare... Bb5 . }
11. Ngf3
11. Nf5( { As mentioned, this is just a nice square as we are very happy with the structure after }12.Bxf5 exf5 { . } )
12. Qe2{ White has to protect the  e3 -square. }
12. Qb6( { Black has other moves as well such as }12...O-O { or }12...Rc8 { but let's show one of Black's key manoeuvres in this position. Attacking  b2  is not really the most important thing about this move.  Instead, Black prepares ... Nd6  and ... Bb5  to exchange the light-squared bishop. With all of White's pawns on dark squares, this is White's most valuable minor piece. } )
13. O-O{ This allows Black's main idea. }( 13.Ne5!? Nd6 14.Nxd7 { is one way to exchange Black's bad bishop before it can land on  b5 . Nevertheless, the game  Martini - Gonda, Budapest 2017  illustrates that Black is not unhappy about this exchange as well. } )
13. Nd6
14. Ne5
14. Bb5{ After the exchange of bishops, White will suffer from their light-squared weaknesses until the end of the game. }
