10. Nf4( { Occupying the  f4 -square is here even stronger than the typical }10...g6 { . }{ White also doesn't have anything special here. Taking on  c6  makes here less sense than in the structure after  8.cxd4  because the c-file is not open. }{    So White usually retreats with }11.Nd3 { to cover the  f4 -square. But Black can just execute the typical manoeuvre }11...Ng7 12.Be2 Nf5⩱ { when Black is also more comfortable because we can win the bishop pair and can eventually play ... e5 . } )
