6. dxc5( { White has nothing else.     A)  }6.Nf3? c4! { drives the bishop back. }7.Be2 Ne4-+ { White has no good way to deal with the pressure against  c3 . } )( {  B)  }6.Nge2?? c4-+ { just loses a piece. } )
6. Nbd7{ Black is keeping the options open whether to recapture on  c5  with the knight or the bishop. }
7. Nge2{ The best move. White plans to recapture on  c3  with the knight to keep the structure intact. }( 7.Nf3 Nxc5 { is just a good position for Black. Even }7...Bxc3 8.bxc3 Nxc5 { is good.  Black can create their counterplay against White's weak pawns. } )
7. a6{ A strong move. Black stops all  Nc3 - b5  ideas and we can take on  c5  next with the bishop. }( 7...Nxc5 8.a3 { does force some concession. Either we have to give up the bishop pair or White can get a little more freedom from their cramped position after something like }8...Ba5 9.b4 Nxd3+ 10.cxd3= { . } )
