5. h5( { The threat   }6...h4 { is very annoying. White has no good response. } )
6. Be2{ This is typically White's move. }( {  A)  }6.f3 Nxe3 { loses a pawn. } )( {  B)  }6.h3 Nxg3 7.fxg3 { is also not what White wants. Their structure is horrible and }7...Qd6 { is already creating some threats. } )
6. h4{ This allows a check on  h5  but the attack against  g3  is the much bigger factor. }
7. Bh5+( 7.Bf4 g5 8.Bh5+ Kd7 { leads to the same position. } )
