9. Nd4{ This is White's main move in practice. The pressure against both  c6  and  e6  reduces Black's options. }( 9.Ng5 { can lead to the same position. We have other options like the immediate }9...Nc7 { but I would recommend just playing }9...Qd7 { as it is the same move against  9.Nd4 . If White does not transpose by taking on  e6  and instead plays }10.O-O { , we are just happy to play }10...Nc7 { , provoking White to take on  e6  or  c6 .     As mentioned, we are usually already very happy with the opening if we just get in ... Bg7  and ... O-O  and in this variation, we are certainly able to achieve this. } )
9. Qd7{ A nice move, protecting  c6  and  e6  both. }
10. Nxe6( { The principled continuation. As usual, if White just plays a slow move like }10.O-O { , we are happy to play }10...Nc7 { , }{ followed by ... Bg7  and ... O-O  with very easy play. } )
10. Qxe6+{ The queen is vulnerable on  e6  against  Bb5 - c4  ideas but we keep our structure intact and White has to give up their right to castle. }
11. Kf1( { The right square. After }11.Kd1 { , the king is more vulnerable to  ...Qg4+  checks which can be a game-changer. For example here, Black can also play }11...Nc7 { , offering a trade of queens because }12.Bc4 Qg4+! { works fine tactically. }{ With the king on  f1 , this variation is not possible. }{   Also }11...Nf4 { or }11...Nxc3+ { are possible because the king on  d1  is more vulnerable. } )
11. O-O-O{ An important move to know. Otherwise, Black is running the risk of being worse. }( {  A)  Don't go }11...Rd8? 12.Bc4! { . Here, Black cannot play }12...Na5 { because of }13.Qb5+ { . } )( {  B)  }11...Nc7? 12.Bc4 { with problems on  f7  and  b7  also doesn't work. } )( { However now after }11...O-O-O { , }{ Black has solved all their problems.  If White takes on  d5 , Black will just have a slightly better endgame. Nevertheless, there might be no way around it. }{ One game continued with }12.d3 Bg7 { when Black was getting ready to get in  ...Nd4  which should end even worse than the endgame after }13.Nxd5 Qxd5 { . } )
