10. Bg7( { Now, Black is threatening to play   }11...Nxg5 12.Nxg5 Nxd4 { . White has to spend a tempo to stop this. } )
11. Be3{ A normal move to overprotect  d4 . }( 11.Bf4 O-O { is similar. } )
11. O-O{ The easiest move. Black just finishes their development.  Now, Black is ready to play .... b6  and break White's queenside structure. Another aggressive idea is ... f7 - f5 - f4  to undermine the position of White's bishop and win space on the kingside. }
