7. cxd5{ This is White's most popular move but Black had no big problems in practice. }
7. Nxd5
8. Bc4{ By far the main move. White tries to keep the tempo up so that Black cannot consolidate. }( 8.Bd3 { , for example, is also playable but Black can just get a decent Anti-IQP position with }8...g6 9.O-O Bg7 { or }8...Bg4 { . } )
8. Be6( { A key move. Black stabilizes  d5  and has the threat of   }9...Nxc3 10.bxc3 Bxc4 { . } )
9. Ng5{ This is a weird move. Black has the choice between a perpetual and the craziest position that you will see in this whole course!     White is threatening to take on  e6  to spoil Black's structure and we cannot move with the bishop because  d5  needs protection. }
9. Nxc3{ This is just forced. }
10. Bxe6{ Yes, White lets their queen hang! }( { The counterattack with }10.Nxe6? { doesn't work. }10...Nxd1 11.Nxd8 Rxd8-+ { Black is a piece up and White cannot recapture the knight because }12.Kxd1 Rxd4+ { picks up the bishop. } )
10. Nxd1{ Once again, we don't really have a choice. }
11. Bxf7+
11. Kd7
12. Be6+( { As White is a queen down, they obviously don't have something better than to repeat if we play }12...Ke8 { . But can Black deviate? } )
12. Kc7{ This is the fighting move. We are a queen up and even if White picks up the knight on  d1 , it is just a minor piece against her majesty.  It is really a fascinating position. The engine evaluates this as equal without any really forced move repetitions. }
13. Bf4+{ White develops with tempo. }
13. Kb6
14. Rxd1{ White has now one knight for the queen but we have won one tempo to hide our king on  a7 . }
14. Ka7{ Now our king is relatively safe. I feel slightly dumb continuing this ridiculous line that you might never see on your board but the next two moves seem to be forced, so I will include those as well. }
15. d5{ Logical. White is attacking the knight on  c6  and prepares  Be3 +. }
15. Qa5+{ This seems to be a subtlety to misplace White's bishop. }
16. Bd2
16. Nb4{ with a complete mess. We would like to finish our development with ... g6  and ... Bg7 . It seems White has enough compensation for the huge amount of material as Black's pieces are currently really restricted. }
