1. c4
1. c6( { In this chapter, we will look at independent move orders after   }1.c4 c6 { that neither transpose to the  Panov chapters  nor to variations from our  1.d4 -part.     I think the only tricky move order is White playing a  double fianchetto  as we can't really trust our ... Bf5  & ... Ne4  setups when White's pawn is not on  d4  yet. I would recommend studying these lines in detail but despite that, there is not much White can do to us. } )
