1. Nf3( { Against }1.Nf3 { , we are pretty free in our move order. As White is not supporting  e2-e4  in any way, we can reach the variations in this chapter both via }1...d5 { as well as }1...Nf6 { .    I decided to go with }1...d5 { as the main move order in this chapter as I believe that there is nothing more natural for a Slav player than to put the d-pawn in the center as soon as possible! } )
1. d5
2. e3
2. Nf6
3. b3{ Nakamura's speciality:  Nf3 ,  e3  and  b3  against everything.  In the last chapter, we have already seen that - with  c2 - c4  and ... c7 - c6  included - White has nothing better than to transpose to  Hikaru's Follwers  with a quick  d2 - d4 . The same logic applies here as well. }
3. g6{ Going the Schlechter route. }
4. Bb2
4. Bg7{ Both sides develop their pieces. White should now or on the next move play  c2 - c4  to provoke ... c7 - c6 . }
5. Be2( { Besides }5.d4 { and }5.c4 { which will transpose to other lines, the only logical move that I can think of. } )
5. O-O{ I want to follow my rule to castle as soon as possible against all  e3  setups. }( { But let me point out that the immediate }5...c5!? { is certainly also a valid idea. } )
6. O-O{ The last flexible move that White has. }( { If White plays }6.c4 { right now, the least thing we can already do is to simply play }6...e6 { when we will play all the typical moves ... b6 , ... Bb7 , ... Nbd7 , ... Qe7  next, but we might have saved a full tempo on ... c6  and go ... c7 - c5  in one move. } )
6. b6{ The most in the spirit of our repertoire. }
7. d3( { A very passive setup for White but at least something different! }7.c4 { is still answered with }7...e6 { . } )
7. Bb7
8. Nbd2
8. c5( { Here, it is Black who is taking the space in the center as White didn't put any pressure on us. On the next move we will most likely play   }9...Nc6 { and, if White doesn't do anything about it, we would also keep advancing with }-- 10...d4 { .    }{ Obviously, White's position is not so bad that they have to allow this but at least it should be obvious that Black has a very good position. } )
