7. d4{ If Black can consolidate the space advantage, we will be much better. }
8. b4{ This is White's main move to weaken Black's center. Typically, White continues to take on  c5  eventually which is the traditional follow-up to eliminate Black's central pawns.  Modern engines also like the idea of just grabbing space with  b4 - b5  in some positions. }
8. Re8{ Black is ready to answer  bxc5  with ... e5 . The  c5 -pawn will be regained later on. }
9. d3{ White just keeps developing. }
9. e5( { This was Black's idea. Now,   }10...cxb4 { is a valid threat. } )
