10. Na6{ Black will just pick up the pawn on  c5  and have a fine position with a lot of space. }
11. Nbd2
11. Nxc5
12. Ba3{ The best move. The bishop on  b2  was extremely miserable and exchanging it against the knight on  c5 , can be an idea to activate some pieces with  Nf3 - g5 - e4 . }
12. Qc7{ Protecting the knight. }
13. Ng5{ This is the main move. White wants to exchange some pieces on  e4  to reduce the pressure on their position. }( 13.Bxc5 Qxc5 14.Ng5 { was played in the modern Correspondence game Owens - Stubbs, 2021. The ideas are similar but after }14...Qe7 15.Nge4 Nd7! { , Black is ready to play  ...f5  next. White's idea was to follow up with the pawn sacrifice }16.c5! Nxc5 17.Nxc5 Qxc5=∞ { which gives the pawn to get good squares for the remaining pieces. This is a standard idea in these structures but also pretty much forced as White would be worse without it.  And even after the pawn sacrifice, this is not a position that should frighten us. } )
13. h6{ It looks slightly unintuitive to provoke White to do what they intended to do anyway. The point is that White should no longer with taking on  c5 . }
14. Nge4( { The best move. }14.Bxc5 hxg5! { is Black's idea. White is forced to retreat and after that, we can once again stop  Nd2-e4 . }15.Ba3 Bf5!⩱ { White's knight on  d2  is still very restricted and Black has ideas like ... g4  to imprison White's kingside even more or to play ... e4  to open the center aggressively at some point. } )
14. Ncxe4{ Black has nothing better than to exchange twice. }
15. Nxe4{ White's knight is threatening to come to  d6  so we should take. }
15. Nxe4
16. Bxe4
16. Rb8{ Unpinning and overprotecting the b-pawn. White did a decent job of exchanging two pair of knights which make the space disadvantage less of a factor.  Nevertheless, it should give us a very pleasant game. Next, we can try to exchange light-squared bishops, for example with ... Bc8 - d7 - c6 . The space advantage gives us the option to play on both sides of the board, like ... b5  or ... h7 - h5 - h4 . }
