1. --{ Enough theory! Here you can see the Grünfeld Slav in action.     I tried to represent each chapter. You can imagine that it was impossible to find good games for every single one because of the rarity of some variations, but for most chapters my search was successful.     Not all games are perfect and, sometimes, I had to resort to online blitz games I found in the Lichess database. In some instances, I became creative and changed the last moves of the games, for example, if a player achieved an advantage through good play but then chose the wrong approach to convert it. Nevertheless, I always gave the real continuation in the clickables and, in the end, I am quite satisfied with my selection.     When it comes to sample games, my main goal is to find games that convey typical ideas and continuations. Engine-based analysis I have generally included only where I felt it was important for the understanding of the position.    Enjoy! }
