1. d4{ This game shows a typical way how these gambit lines can go: Black overprotects his structure and doesn't allow any tricks.  White is then in a tough spot. Still going for tactical options even though they objectively don't work out - as we have seen in the last example - or to continue with normal developing moves when Black will eventually have all pieces developed and be ready for ... c6 - c5 . }
