6. a6{ A good moment to point out that the game started with a slightly different move order where Black played ... a7 - a6  much earlier. }( { In the given position, there is no immediate need for }6...a6 { and while it is a useful move in general, starting with }6...e6 { looks much more flexible. } )
7. Qc2{ In the next moves we see, that White understands that all concrete ideas like  b2 - b3  or  e3 - e4  - with ideas like  e4 - e5  or  d4 - d5  - would only make matters worse and so he simply kept developing. }
7. e6{ Black does the same. }
8. Be2
