9. Nbd7{ As you can see, there is not much to see. However, - even though Black might start with ... Be7  and ... O-O  , he is also ready to play ... c5  when he wants.  In the game, White does now start to fight against this idea but even though he delays it for many moves, none of his measures is more than temporary and at some point the ... c5 -break comes. }
10. Ne4{ Trying to take control over the  c5 -square. Also, by clearing the c-file, White might be able to play  b2 - b3  under good circumstances.  But Black is up to the task. }
10. Nxe4( { The immediate }10...c5 { shows White's idea. }11.Nxc5 Nxc5 12.dxc5 Bxc5 13.b3 { Even here, Black is better but at least White might regain his pawn. } )
11. Qxe4{ Now, the  c6 -pawn is pinned. }
11. Nf6
12. Qc2
