1. d4{ A very instructive game. White, a strong and very solid Grandmaster, doesn't remember the correct theory and is significantly worse with White after move 9. It was not a classical game but one in a serious rapid tournament }
1. d5
2. Nf3
2. Nf6
3. c4
3. c6
4. Qc2{ White plays  'Schlechter's Dream' . This game nicely illustrates why I named this line like this. }
4. g6
