16. Rb8{ I believe, in general, it is a pretty smart idea to just keep the b-pawn protected instead of moving it. This avoids weaknesses on the queenside.  The engine does not completely agree with this move but White has to be extremely precise while Black's counterplay on the other side can become quite menacing. }( 16...b6 17.Na6 Rc8⇆ { is the engine recommendation to play objectively the best moves. With our queenside slightly weakened, our autopilot kingside attack with ... e6 - e5 - e4 , ... f6 - f5 - f4 , ... g6 - g5  is much riskier because White should be quicker on the kingside than in the game.  So, you better combine this approach with fighting back on the kingside. ... Rf7 , ... Qb7 , ... Na5 - c4 , potentially, doubling on the c-file is certainly not a bad position for Black. } )
