4. g6{ If you are a fan of the Grünfeld Slav, you have to be a fan of Salo Flohr!     These days, many people might not know much about him, but in the 1930s, he was considered one of the strongest players in the world. He was supposed to play a World Championship match against Alekhine in 1939 but the Second World War stopped those plans. And he played the Schlechter!     As you can see in this game, he even played it against the White's most flexible setup with  3.Nf3  and  4.Nc3 . Here, you can see a Classic where he beat Ex-World Champion Max Euwe with Black in under 30 moves! }
