26. Rae7
27. g3
27. g5{ At some point, Black has to play this move to increase the pressure. }( 27...h5? 28.h4 { would close down everything. } )
28. Qh5
28. gxf4{ I guess both players assumed that White has to recapture with the g-pawn. }( 28...h6 { , just to keep the tension, was better. } )
29. gxf4( 29.exf4! { was actually the right move. It looks horribly dangerous, especially because the  d4 -pawn is hanging with check but Black cannot really grab it. and White is actually threatening 30.  Qxe8 + . }29...Rxe1+ 30.Rxe1 Rxe1+ 31.Bxe1 Qxd4+? 32.Bf2! { is actually better for White because White's queen will invade next. } )
29. Qg6+{ Black goes for an advantageous endgame where White's weak pawns give Black an advantage. }( 29...Rxe3!? 30.Qxe8+! Rxe8 31.Rxe8+ Kf7 32.Rxc8 { is the reason why Black didn't take the pawn. Even though }32...Qg6+ { , followed by ... Qg4  or .... Bxf4  is still dangerous for White. } )
